Author: dukeleto#7326
Content: with -ac_nk and -ac_blocktime, I think KMD can re-create just about every equihash coin that exists, via CLI parameters. That opens up which coins would be open to migrating to an AC, since we could support their N,K and blocktime. Before, we could only do 200,9, and it would be a non-starter for chains that changed those values

Content: Yeah I figured whe I was making the ac_nk, that only using the n/k % 8 limitaion was pretty usless, lucky the BEAM project had c++ code that allows that limitation to be removed, so I just ported that to KMD allowing any number to be used.  Ive been suing 77/3 on LABS test chains for months, as its "asic" and "gpu" resitant and used very little resources to mine.
